## Error Handling

### Exception Hierarchy

```
KafkaException (base for all Kafka exceptions)
├── RetriableException (broker may retry)
├── NonRetriableException (broker won't retry)
└── (specific subtypes below)
```

### Common Exception Types

#### CommitFailedException

```java
try {
    consumer.commitSync();
} catch (CommitFailedException e) {
    // Commit failed - consumer likely lost ownership of partitions
    // Usually due to rebalance or timeout
    log.error("Commit failed - may have lost partition ownership", e);
    // Cannot retry - state unknown
}
```

**Causes:**
- Consumer removed from group due to timeout
- Rebalance occurred, partitions reassigned
- Authorization failure
- Broker-side error

**Recovery:** Cannot retry from consumer side; rejoin group or restart.

#### RetriableCommitFailedException

```java
consumer.commitAsync((offsets, exception) -> {
    if (exception instanceof RetriableCommitFailedException) {
        // Safe to retry
        log.warn("Retriable commit failure, will retry");
        consumer.commitAsync(offsets, this);  // Retry
    } else if (exception != null) {
        // Non-retriable error
        log.error("Permanent commit failure", exception);
    }
});
```

**Causes:**
- Coordinator not available
- Broker temporary failure
- Request timeout

**Recovery:** Can retry with backoff.

#### WakeupException

```java
// In consumer thread
try {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
    // ... process records ...
} catch (WakeupException e) {
    log.info("Consumer woken up");
    // Clean up and break polling loop
    consumer.close();
    System.exit(0);
}

// In another thread
Thread consumerThread = new Thread(() -> {
    // ... polling loop ...
});
consumerThread.start();

// Later, wake up consumer
consumer.wakeup();  // Safe to call from any thread
consumerThread.join();
```

**Semantics:**
- Only exception safe to throw from outside consumer thread
- Interrupts blocking `poll()` without advancing offset
- Must be caught and handled explicitly
- Useful for graceful shutdown

#### InterruptException

```java
try {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
} catch (InterruptException e) {
    // Thread was interrupted (via Thread.interrupt())
    log.info("Consumer thread interrupted");
    Thread.currentThread().interrupt();  // Re-interrupt
}
```

**Semantics:**
- Raised if thread is interrupted while blocked in `poll()`
- Clears thread interrupt flag
- Different from `WakeupException` (which is a KafkaException)

#### OffsetOutOfRangeException

```java
try {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
} catch (OffsetOutOfRangeException e) {
    // Committed offset is outside valid range [beginOffset, endOffset)
    Set<TopicPartition> affectedPartitions = e.partitions();

    // Recovery: seek to valid offset
    for (TopicPartition tp : affectedPartitions) {
        consumer.seekToEnd(Arrays.asList(tp));
        // Or: consumer.seekToBeginning(Arrays.asList(tp));
    }

    // Retry poll
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
}
```

**Causes:**
- Committed offset deleted due to retention policy
- Topic was compacted
- Committed offset was never valid

**Recovery:** Seek to valid offset (beginning/end) and resume.

#### NoOffsetForPartitionException

```java
try {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
} catch (NoOffsetForPartitionException e) {
    // No committed offset for partition and auto.offset.reset="none"
    Set<TopicPartition> affectedPartitions = e.partitions();

    // Recovery: manually seek to valid offset
    for (TopicPartition tp : affectedPartitions) {
        consumer.seekToBeginning(Arrays.asList(tp));
    }
}
```

**Causes:**
- First time consuming from partition (no prior commit)
- `auto.offset.reset="none"` configured
- Committed offset was explicitly cleared

**Recovery:** Seek to valid offset manually.

#### RecordDeserializationException

```java
try {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
    // Records returned up to (but NOT including) bad record
    for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
        process(record);
    }
} catch (RecordDeserializationException e) {
    // Deserialization failed for record at e.offset()
    TopicPartition tp = e.topicPartition();
    long badOffset = e.offset();

    log.error("Deserialization failed at " + tp + ":" + badOffset);

    // Recovery: skip bad record and continue
    long position = consumer.position(tp);  // = badOffset
    consumer.seek(tp, badOffset + 1);  // Skip bad record
}
```

**Important semantics:**
- `poll()` returns records up to (not including) bad record
- Position stops at bad record (allows inspection/skipping)
- Consumer can skip bad record and resume
- Useful for robustness (don't crash on bad data)

#### RecordTooLargeException

```java
try {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
} catch (RecordTooLargeException e) {
    // Record size exceeds fetch.message.max.bytes
    // Cannot be fetched without increasing broker config
    log.error("Record too large to fetch", e);
    // Manual recovery: admin API to inspect/delete offending record
}
```

**Causes:**
- Record larger than `fetch.message.max.bytes` (must match broker config)
- Broker-side limit, cannot be overcome by client alone

**Recovery:** Increase broker-side `replica.fetch.max.bytes` and `message.max.bytes` (requires broker restart).

#### AuthorizationException

```java
try {
    consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("orders"));
} catch (AuthorizationException e) {
    // User not authorized to read from topic
    log.error("Not authorized to read from topic", e);
}
```

**Causes:**
- User/principal lacks read permission
- ACL not configured correctly
- SASL authentication failed

**Recovery:** Check security configuration and user permissions.

